3.4 Variables
=============

The syntax of Pedro variables fall into two categories.
  1. An upper case letter or "_" followed by any sequence consisting of
     "_" and alphanumeric characters.

     Examples:
          X, X_23, _fred_12
  2. The "anonymous" variable "_"

   Note that repeated occurrences of a variable token of the first
category in a string representing a Pedro term represent the same
variable.  This is not the case for anonymous variables: each occurrence
represents a different variable.


