12.1 C API
==========

The directory 'src/c_api' contains a C-level API for Pedro clients (not
using glib) in the files 'c_api.c', 'c_api.h', 'pedro_token.c' and
'pedro_token.h'.

   The directory also contains four example programs in two pairs.  The
program 'producer.c' sends notifications entered by the user.  The
program 'consumer.c' subscribes based on information entered by the user
and displays received notifications.

   The programs 'ping.c' and 'pong.c' respectively registers the names
'ping' and 'pong'.  The program 'ping.c' repeatedly asks for a term from
the user, sends it as a peer-to-peer message to 'pong' and waits for a
reply message and displays it.  The program 'pong.c' repeatedly waits
for a peer-to-peer message, and replies with the same message wrapped in
a structured term whose functor is 'echo'.

   The file 'c_api.h' contains comments describing the API.srsrc


